    <description>
      <biogHist id="md5-e5cd20a0c219dcd01caf2d2133903221">
        <p>English scholar, 1898-1986.  Professor Jones completed his honours BA in English (1921) at the  University of Alberta, and became a rural teacher, 1920-1922, then professor in the Department of  English, 1928-1953.  He became head of the Department (1953-1961), retiring in 1964.  During  World War II he served in the army.  His favorite poet was John Milton, in whose writings he gave  courses at the senior and graduate levels.</p>
      </biogHist>
